# Rotate in place to an ABSOLUTE target heading (radians, IMU/ENU frame — the
# same frame quaternion_to_yaw(/mavros/imu/data) produces, shared by the
# mission node and yaw_controller_node). Blocking: the response comes back
# only once the rotation has settled on target or timed out. This is the same
# rotate_to_heading() loop the /hightide/yaw_spin style spin uses for its
# return-to-heading, so callers get identical, single-source behavior.
float64 target_heading
float64 timeout_sec        # 0 = use the node's default rotate timeout
---
bool success
string message
